-- Private Pensions to Charge 15% Withholding Tax, Milliyet Reports
-- B y   S i b e l   A k b a y
-- 2012-09-07T07:47:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/private-pensions-to-charge-15-withholding-tax-milliyet-reports.html
Private pension companies will
charge a 15 percent withholding tax on returns, instead of
capital, from people who leave the plan before 10 years,
 Milliyet  newspaper reported, citing a decree published in the
Official Gazette yesterday.  According to the decree, people leaving the plan after 10
years but before retirement will pay 10 percent withholding tax
and those who retire will pay 5 percent tax, Milliyet said. The
new legislation was part of a law the government recently
implemented to increase  Turkey â€™s savings rate, the Istanbul-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
